@LHCGreg Most likely in the next release of buildah and `4.1` of podman (if this gets merged today) https://github.com/containers/buildah/pull/3947. I'll notify you whenever this PR is out.

> Debian repository but that now seems to be a few versions behind, even in the 3.x line. Current version there is podman 3.4.2 while the latest 3.x release seems to be 3.4.7. https://podman.io/getting-started/installation only mentions the main Debian repository which is even older, 3.0.1. Is building from source the only option?

Ah i see debian release is running few versions behind but no issues I think building from source is not so difficult https://podman.io/getting-started/installation#building-from-scratch . You can always open issues/discussions on `buildah/podman` repo if you need any help with this.
